cy => Agentic. MULTI-STEP: single classification step per call, not a multi-agent pipeline. Rejection-gate: Workflow rejected because behavior does not chain multiple agentic decisions; one model decision per call is evaluated.","test_description":"Run repeated real classifications for the same document/taxonomy over a controlled window, log provider raw responses and final labels, and assert label changes only coincide with observed provider-response changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Request construction enforces the configured token budget before dispatch (for example truncate/reject according to policy).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure often occurs at boundary between token-budget logic and dispatch gating (oversized request accidentally sent). REAL-INFRA: no real network/OS needed; in-process tokenizer/config + fake dispatcher can verify pre-dispatch enforcement. MOCK-HIDE: if dispatch is mocked at too abstract a level, send/no-send bugs can be hidden; capture actual call/no-call and built payload. LLM-DEP: no dependence on model output content. MULTI-STEP: none. Rejection-gate: System rejected because behavior is explicitly \"before dispatch\" policy enforcement, reproducible without real HTTP.","test_description":"Configure a tight budget, pass an over-budget document, and assert policy outcome (truncate or reject) plus dispatch behavior (modified payload sent or call blocked) via a recording fake client.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: provider-reported usage is produced by the real AI API/tokenizer; local fakes can mask real counting differences. REAL-INFRA: real external call required. MOCK-HIDE: mocked usage values trivially pass and cannot catch provider-side tokenization/accounting mismatches. LLM-DEP: execution path depends on real AI/ML API response fields; per guidance, keep Agentic unless only wiring is tested. Here correctness is about real provider usage outcome. MULTI-STEP: no multi-agent sequence. Rejection-gate: Integration rejected because behavior text requires \"provider-reported\" usage; System considered but Agentic retained since the decisive risk is real model/API output characteristics, not merely HTTP transport.","test_description":"Invoke the real provider on representative documents with production prompt/template settings and assert reported total tokens are <= configured budget; fail on any over-budget call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.23,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is in retry/backoff orchestration across caller, API client, and timing/retry policy modules. REAL-INFRA: can be reproduced with in-process fake provider returning rate-limit errors then success; real network not required for core failure. MOCK-HIDE: simplistic success-only mocks hide retry logic bugs, so sequence-aware stub is needed. LLM-DEP: no dependence on model output quality/content; this is transport/error-handling behavior. MULTI-STEP: retries are control-flow repeats, not multiple agentic decision stages. Rejection-gate: System rejected because behavior text concerns handling a rate-limit signal, which a deterministic stub can emulate; Agentic rejected because no model judgment is asserted.","test_description":"Use